  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Promoter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>As a Promoter, you will represent our brand in retail environments by engaging customers to demonstrate and promote consumer electronic products, delivering excellent customer experiences, and achieving sales goals.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Engage walk-in customers to demonstrate and explain features of consumer electronic products to increase interest and sales</li><li>Provide accurate product information and recommend suitable products based on customer needs to improve conversion rates</li><li>Offer post-sale customer support to enhance customer satisfaction and loyalty</li><li>Respond to customer questions in a pleasant and professional manner to maintain positive brand image</li><li>Maintain clean, well-stocked, and visually appealing product displays to attract customers and support sales</li><li>Achieve or exceed daily and monthly sales targets and performance KPIs through effective customer engagement and sales techniques</li><li>Manage customer concerns professionally and resolve issues to ensure a positive shopping experience</li><li>Work retail hours including weekends and public holidays to support store operations and customer service</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum GCE “N” / “O” Level education</li><li>1–2 years of relevant experience in retail, sales promotion, or selling consumer electronics</li><li>Strong communication skills demonstrated through effective customer interactions</li><li>Friendly, energetic, and service-oriented personality to engage customers and build rapport</li><li>Strong understanding of sales principles and customer service practices to drive sales performance</li><li>Able to work under pressure and resolve customer concerns professionally</li><li>Willing to work retail hours including weekends and public holidays</li></ul>",
